# Non-Functional Requirements

## Introduction

This document outlines the non-functional requirements of the Society360 â€“ Smart Residential Management System. These requirements define the quality attributes, performance standards, security expectations, and operational constraints of the system.

---

## 1. Security Requirements

### NFR-1.1 Authentication Security
- All users shall authenticate using secure credentials.
- Passwords shall be stored using strong hashing mechanisms.

### NFR-1.2 Authorization
- Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) shall be enforced across all modules.
- Users shall only access features permitted to their assigned role.

### NFR-1.3 Data Protection
- Sensitive personal and financial data shall be securely stored.
- API endpoints shall validate and sanitize all input data.

### NFR-1.4 Session Security
- User sessions shall be securely managed and invalidated on logout.
- Unauthorized session access shall be prevented.

---

## 2. Performance Requirements

### NFR-2.1 Response Time
- The system shall respond to user requests within acceptable time limits under normal load.

### NFR-2.2 Concurrent Users
- The system shall support multiple concurrent users without performance degradation.

---

## 3. Scalability Requirements

### NFR-3.1 Horizontal Scalability
- The system architecture shall allow scaling to accommodate growth in users and data.

### NFR-3.2 Modular Design
- Modules shall be loosely coupled to support future enhancements.

---

## 4. Reliability & Availability

### NFR-4.1 System Availability
- The system shall be available during standard operational hours with minimal downtime.

### NFR-4.2 Data Integrity
- The system shall ensure consistency and integrity of stored data.

---

## 5. Usability Requirements

### NFR-5.1 User-Friendly Interface
- The interface shall be simple, intuitive, and accessible to non-technical users.

### NFR-5.2 Responsive Design
- The system shall be usable across desktop, tablet, and mobile devices.

---

## 6. Maintainability

### NFR-6.1 Code Quality
- The codebase shall follow clean coding standards and best practices.

### NFR-6.2 Documentation
- System architecture and usage shall be well documented.

---

## 7. Compatibility

### NFR-7.1 Browser Compatibility
- The system shall support modern web browsers.

---

## 8. Compliance

### NFR-8.1 Organizational Guidelines
- The system shall strictly adhere to Civora Nexus Pvt. Ltd. branding and design standards.

---

## Conclusion

The non-functional requirements ensure that Society360 delivers a secure, reliable, scalable, and user-friendly platform that meets industry-quality standards and operational expectations.
